attributes.description: Events are generated from endpoints to troubleshoot if devices are connected to an endpoint and if they are being allowed or blocked.  Use this dashboard to find hardware identifiers to add to your whitelist.

embeddableConfig.description: Shows the history of device attachment events being reported over time.
When devices attempt to connect TYCHON will report on that data so administrators can make decisions to allow that device to connect if its being denied.
Use these device IDs to update the whitelist in policy which will allow that USB device to connect to the computer it's being attached to.
The assets that have reported this information to the dashboard.

attributes.title: [TYCHON] - Device Control Events
